<h2 id="adding-pinky-flourish-to-chord-shapes">Adding pinky flourish to chord shapes</h2>

<p>A final technique I use in the â€œadvancedâ€ riff is that of using your left-hand pinky to add a flourish note to the fingerpicking. The idea is, start with the familiar foundation chord shape - and then for one of the 4-note-fingerpicking-sequences, play that foundation shape with your pinky down. Then play the sequence again, with your pinky lifted. This creates a nice sound of variety and suggested melody.</p>

